  "prompt": "How can you close a gap in your teeth without braces?",
  "response": "There are several ways to close a gap in teeth without traditional braces:\n\n1. Dental Bonding\n- Quick procedure\n- Uses tooth-colored resin\n- Relatively inexpensive\n- Can be completed in one visit\n\n2. Dental Veneers\n- Thin porcelain or composite shells\n- Cover the front of teeth\n- Permanent solution\n- Can improve overall appearance\n\n3. Invisalign\n- Clear, removable aligners\n- Less noticeable than metal braces\n- Gradually shifts teeth\n- More comfortable than traditional braces\n\n4. Dental Crowns\n- Covers entire tooth\n- Can reshape and close small gaps\n- More invasive procedure\n\n5. Dental Bands\n- Temporary at-home solution\n- Elastic bands can slowly push teeth together\n- Less expensive option\n- Not recommended without professional consultation\n\n6. Cosmetic Contouring\n- Reshaping teeth\n- Minimal tooth removal\n- Can help with minor gaps\n\n7. Dental Implants\n- Permanent solution for larger gaps\n- Replaces missing teeth\n- More expensive option\n\nImportant: Consult a dentist to determine the best method for your specific situation, as each approach has pros and cons depending on individual dental conditions.",
